Hi @Gitward!

Tablesorter binds to the header cells, so when you remove any cells in the `thead` you essentially need to rebind to the header cells. This can be done in one of these three ways:

1. Completely reinitialize tablesorter. Meaning, [destroy](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#destroy) it then re-apply it.

    ```js
    // pass a false boolean to *not* remove the 
    // "tablesorter" class name to prevent a FOUC
    // .trigger("destroy", [removeAllClasses, callback]);
    $("#table").trigger("destroy", [false, function(){
        // reinitialize tablesorter
        $("#table").tablesorter();
    }]);
    ```

2. It might be easier to wrap the table in a `<div id="wrapper">...</div>`, or something similar. Then use `$("#wrapper").empty();` to clear out the table. But, there is an issue with a memory leak (#1034) using this method that I can't seem to isolate.

3. Lastly, there is an ["updateAll" method](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#updateall) which can be used when modifying both the `<thead>` and `<tbody>` content, but it has not been well optimized to work with all widgets. I don't know which widgets you're using, so please test this method carefully.

I'm not sure which method would work best in your case so try each one out and see

