@takluyver, my best guess:

Before #332, "invalid" default values could be defined by leverage the fact that defaults assigned via a trait's constructor where never cross-validated.

In the case of `pre_save_hook`, the constructor default is `None`, which now raises an error because `None` isn't callable.

