Just a follow-up to the above: an alternative to dynamic generation (of either URLs or URL names) is to explicitly hard-code the meta-data for every resource we access. I would personally like the explicitness of that - it becomes totally clear how the client code relates to the server code. We could even define the expected meta-data of our models in a way analogous to Vue.js props.

I could imagine something like:

```javascript
const classroom = new Resources.Model({
  url: '/api_v1/learn/classroom/{id}',
  props: {
    name: String,
    members: Array,
  }
});

const classroomCollection = new Resource.Collection({
  url: '/api_v1/learn/classroom',
  model: classroom,
});
```

